onChange.script:
import time
	
	#Setting Components Visiablity and Display and Basis
	self.view.custom.LoadingVisibility = True
	self.view.custom.InstanceVisibility = False
	
	#Multiplying Instances by the Avg Load Time
	sleepTimer = self.view.custom.InstantCount * 1.7
	
	#Pausing the thread to allow Instances to Load
	time.sleep(sleepTimer)
	
	#Setting Components Visiablity and Display and Basis
	self.view.custom.LoadingVisibility = False
	self.view.custom.InstanceVisibility = True

config.script:
import time
	
	#Setting Components Visiablity and Display and Basis
	self.getChild("loading").position.display = True
	self.getChild("Row2").meta.visible = False
	self.getChild("Row2").position.basis = 0
	
	#Multiplying Instances by the Avg Load Time
	sleepTimer = self.view.custom.InstantCount * 2.2
	
	#Pausing the thread to allow Instances to Load
	time.sleep(sleepTimer)
	
	#Setting Components Visiablity and Display and Basis
	self.getChild("loading").position.display = False
	self.getChild("Row2").meta.visible = True
	self.getChild("Row2").position.basis = "100%"

messageHandlers.script:
# implement your handler here
	newCount = 0
	finishedCount = self.view.custom.FinishedCount
	newCount = self.view.custom.FinishedCount + 1
	system.perspective.print(finishedCount)
	system.perspective.print(newCount)
	system.perspective.print(self.view.custom.InstantCount)
	self.view.custom.FinishedCount = newCount
	if newCount == self.view.custom.InstantCount:
		system.perspective.closePopup('spinner')
